y of the Retropharyngeal abscess post\nneck showing enlarged traumatic (foreign body ingestion)\nadenoid encroaching upon or in case of complicated tonsillitis\nthe nasopharyngeal air way or pharyngitis\nWHEN SHOULD CT BE ORDERED IN HEAD AND NECK?\nCT is excellent in evaluation of:\n1. Sinusitis; it can differentiate between acute and chronic sinusitis and can\ndetect sinonasal polyposis and retention cysts.\nAcute sinusitis: frothy\nChronic sinusitis: opacified sinuses\nsecretions and air fluid level\nand sclerosing of bone.\n48"}